<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-masterpages.asp">Master Pages in ASP.NET Whidbey</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Create consistent Web sites with ease using the new MasterPages feature in ASP.NET Whidbey.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-meetwebpartfrmwrk.asp">Meet the Web Part Framework</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Create Web applications easily with these powerful new ASP.NET Whidbey controls.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-standardize-masterpages.asp">Standardize Your Site Fast With Master Pages</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Learn how to apply MasterPages with ASP.NET Whidbey to quickly standardize your site. ASP.NET Whidbey includes a flexible page-template system with excellent visual-designer support.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />
</p>

<h3><a name='caching'>Caching</a></h3>
<p>


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-createcacheconfigobject.asp">Make a Cache Configuration Object for ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Improve reuse of your cached data by encapsulating caching best practices into a helper class. You can manage caching policies across the application and significantly reduce lines of code you'll need.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-cachingtechniquesbestpract.asp">ASP.NET Caching: Techniques and Best Practices</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">ASP.NET provides three forms of caching in Web applications. Examine best practices and techniques for using these three methods to improve your performance.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />
</p>

<h3><a name='state'>State Management</a></h3>
<p>


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-finitestatemachines.asp">Finite State Machines, Wizards and the Web</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Explore a solution for creating Wizards using ASP.NET that step your users through a process. Discover how this feature will become even easier with ASP.NET Whidbey.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/03/02/cuttingedge/toc.asp">The ASP.NET View State</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Take a tour of the view state implementation in ASP.NET and learn how to keep your Web pages fit and trim and a bit more secure.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/converttoaspnet.asp">How to Share Session State Between Classic ASP and ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Share session state between classic ASP and Microsoft ASP.NET for easier conversion of applications.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/01/12/cutting/toc.asp">Using Session and Application Objects in ASP.NET, Part 2</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Discover how ASP.NET expands the capabilities of the Session and Application objects.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/03/05/datapoints/toc.asp">Techniques for Managing Rowset Paging</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Learn techniques for working with multiple pages of data in your ASP.NET application.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnetsessionstate.asp">Explore Session State Implementation in ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Delve into session state implementation in ASP.NET 1.1. Learn to optimize session state management from within managed Web applications.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/msdnmag/issues/03/04/aspnetuserstate/default.aspx">Nine Options for Managing Persistent User State in Your ASP.NET Application</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Learn about techniques, guidelines, and updated best practices on the many ways to persist data between user requests in ASP.NET.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dv_vstechart/html/vbtchaspnetcookies101.asp">Basics of Cookies in ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Get techniques for reading and writing HTTP cookies in an ASP.NET Web application.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />
</p>

<h3><a name='security'>Security & Validation</a></h3>
<p>


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/02/09/aspnethashalgorithms/toc.asp">Tamper-Resistant Apps: Cryptographic Hash Algorithms Let You Detect Malicious Code in ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Use the .NET Framework cryptographic functions from within ASP.NET.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/mixedsecurity.asp">Mixing Forms and Windows Security in ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Examine a solution that combines Forms and Windows Authentication, enabling ASP.NET security for both internal and external users.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/02/04/valid/toc.asp">Selectively Enable Form Validation When Using ASP.NET Web Controls</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Extend the validation capabilities of ASP.NET to control when, and where, validation takes place.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/02/08/aspnetcommerceapp/toc.asp">Leverage the Authentication and Form Validation Features of ASP.NET to Bolster Your Commerce App</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">See how the power and flexibility of ASP.NET's validation controls make it easy to plug new functionality into your Web applications.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/01/11/cutting/toc.asp">Using Session and Application Objects in ASP .NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Discover how ASP.NET expands the capabilities of the Session and Application objects.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspplusvalid.asp">ASP.NET Validation in Depth</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">See a detailed examination of the workings of ASP.NET validation Web controls.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dnnetsec/html/secnetlpMSDN.asp">.NET Security Guide</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Examine a practical, scenario-driven approach to designing and building secure ASP.NET applications for Windows 2000 and the .NET Framework 1.0.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dnbda/html/authaspdotnet.asp">Authentication in ASP.NET: .NET Security Guidance</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Learn how both Internet Information Services and ASP.NET provide security models that allow you to authenticate your users appropriately and obtain the correct security context within your application.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/02/04/aspsec/toc.asp">An Introductory Guide to Building and Deploying More Secure Sites with ASP.NET and IIS</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Learn how ASP.NET uses the .NET Framework Security model to secure your Web applications.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/vbtv/default.asp">MSDN Online - VBTV</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Whether you're an existing Visual Basic developer or a new .NET developer, VBTV provides you with the latest and most pertinent information you need to get up and running quickly with Visual Basic .NET.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/pdc_userinput.asp">User Input Validation in ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Read a brief overview of the validation framework in ASP.NET, and walk through an example on adding validation to a page.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/personalizationwhidbey.asp">Personalization in ASP.NET Whidbey</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Forget about all the code you used to write to add personalization to your Web sites. See the new features in ASP.NET Whidbey that make adding personalization a breeze.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-membership.asp">Add Membership and Role Support with ASP.NET Whidbey</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Discover how you can add membership and role support quickly with ASP.NET Whidbey. Often this doesn't require any code.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-getpersonal.asp">Get Personal with ASP.NET Whidbey</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Reduce development time and code with personalization and membership in ASP.NET Whidbey.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-securingapps.asp">Use Less Code to Secure ASP.NET Applications</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Examine the new security features in ASP.NET Whidbey. They make adding authentication and authorization simple, and almost code-free.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />
</p>

<h3><a name='graphics'>Graphics</a></h3>
<p>


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/colorquant.asp">Optimizing Color Quantization for ASP.NET Images</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Describes how to quantize (recolor) dynamically generated images for ASP.NET pages in order to overcome a limitation of GDI+ in the .NET Framework versions 1.0 and 1.1. This article presents two methods of color depth reduction on images.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/msdnmag/issues/02/02/ASPDraw/TOC.asp">Create Snazzy Web Charts and Graphics On the Fly</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Access the drawing classes of the .NET Framework directly with C# to create dynamic images and charts, and display them by way of ASP.NET.

	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />
</p>

<h3><a name='xml'>XML</a></h3>
<p>


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-createrssw-aspnet.asp">Create an RSS News Aggregator with ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Examine how the XML support in the .NET Framework makes creating an RSS News Aggregator simple.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/02/12/xmlschemaimporting/toc.asp">Take Advantage of Existing External XML Schemas with a Custom Import Framework in ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">This article builds an external schema framework as an extension to the ASP.NET Web Services runtime to enable you to reference external schemas within your XML Web Service interface.

	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/msdnmag/issues/03/03/siteskinning/default.aspx">Site Skinning: Rich XML Classes Let Users Personalize Their Visual Experience on Your ASP.NET Site</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">See an illustration on the use of the rich XML classes in the .NET Framework and the built-in extensibility of ASP.NET to apply the skinning technique to Web sites, wrapping their functionality in a new user interface that allows customers to personalize their experience. 
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />
</p>

<h3><a name='pipeline'>HTTP Runtime</a></h3>
<p>


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/01/07/asp/toc.asp">ASP .NET Connection Model and Writing Custom HTTP Handler/Response Objects</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Learn how to create custom HTTP Handlers and use them to learn how ASP.NET connection model works.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/02/05/asp/toc.asp">HTTP Modules</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Discover how to use HTTP Modules to extend the functionality of ASP.NET.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/dngrftheaspnethttpruntime.asp">The ASP.NET HTTP Runtime</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Dino Esposito looks at the constituent components of the HTTP runtime, the logic that drives the processing of individual requests directed to ASP.NET applications, and shows all the steps by which a HTTP request becomes plain HTML text.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/dnaspp/html/aspnet-pageobjectmodel.asp">One Day in the Life of an ASP.NET Web Page</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Explore the eventing model built around ASP.NET Web pages and the various stages that a Web page experiences on its way to HTML. Discover the events that characterize the lifecycle of page and how control and page authors can intervene to alter the standard behavior.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/02/08/httpfilters/toc.asp"> Intercept, Monitor, and Modify Web Requests with HTTP Filters in ISAPI and ASP.NET </a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Examine how HTTP Modules compare to ISAPI Filters, and see how to create one to reroute incoming Web Requests.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://www.msdn.microsoft.com/msdnmag/issues/03/06/threading/toc.asp">Use Threads and Build Asynchronous Handlers in Your Server-Side Web Code</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Learn the benefits, tradeoffs and choices for using threads from your ASP.NET applications.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
<p />


<span style="display:inline-block;">
<a style="font-weight:bold;" href="/asp.net/default.aspx?pull=/msdnmag/issues/02/09/httppipelines/default.aspx">Securely Implement Request Processing, Filtering, and Content Redirection with HTTP Pipelines in ASP.NET</a><br />


	<span style="color:#000000;">Explore the architecture of the lower-level infrastructure of ASP.NET and how you can use this pipeline to add sophisticated functionality to an ASP.NET-based application.
	</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;


</span>
